149
00:10:22,520 --> 00:10:24,880
Right.

150
00:10:24,880 --> 00:10:26,640
I'm not into love.

151
00:10:26,640 --> 00:10:29,080
Come on.

152
00:10:29,080 --> 00:10:31,820
This movie is made for people to be into it.

153
00:10:31,820 --> 00:10:34,360
Not for you.

154
00:10:34,360 --> 00:10:36,240
Let's Rock Paper Scissors. Get it over with.

155
00:10:36,240 --> 00:10:39,120
No way. That's too sloppy.

156
00:10:39,120 --> 00:10:41,310
How about this?

157
00:10:41,310 --> 00:10:43,320
We meet halfway.

158
00:10:43,320 --> 00:10:47,840
They part for so long and meet once again.

159
00:10:47,840 --> 00:10:50,110
What do you think?

160
00:10:50,110 --> 00:10:52,190
Is that happy or unhappy?

161
00:10:52,190 --> 00:10:53,870
Open ending.

162
00:10:53,870 --> 00:10:57,760
Tess, I like that ending.

163
00:10:57,760 --> 00:11:00,813
I'll go with it. Let's do it.

164
00:11:00,813 --> 00:11:03,290
Our job is done. Relieved.

165
00:11:03,290 --> 00:11:04,890
I'll go pee now.

166
00:11:04,890 --> 00:11:06,740
I'm coming, too.

167
00:11:06,740 --> 00:11:08,140
Sure.

168
00:11:09,340 --> 00:11:10,990
I just talked to my dad.

169
00:11:10,990 --> 00:11:14,600
This Friday, we'll present him with the film treatment.

170
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:16,000
Awesome.

171
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:18,755
Go home and handle our own section of the presentation.

172
00:11:18,755 --> 00:11:21,277
Huh? What presentation?

173
00:11:21,277 --> 00:11:22,770
Why are you confused?

174
00:11:22,770 --> 00:11:24,400
Our responsibility.

175
00:11:24,400 --> 00:11:27,120
